</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F603691FFB30D3D1A8BF8DD1500FF37" blockId="14.[151,1437,1676,2028]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,321]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="466" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis id="6DABEA83FFB30D3C1A8BF8DD1535F8BA" bold="true" box="[199,298,1857,1883]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">Habitat.</emphasis>
This species has usually been found in streams without aquatic vegetation, in slow-moving water and in shaded areas (
<bibRefCitation id="3B4E4B60FFB30D3C1B02F8F91628F89E" author="Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. de" box="[334,567,1893,1919]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" refId="ref55178" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. de (1997) Os Heteropteros aquaticos de Minas Gerais. Guia introdutorio com chave de identificacao para as especies de Nepomorpha e Gerromorpha. Editora Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais, Belo Horizonte, 177 pp." type="book" year="1997">Nieser &amp; Melo 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3B4E4B60FFB30D3C180EF8F91735F89E" author="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N." box="[578,810,1893,1919]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="43 - 49" refId="ref52862" refString="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N. (2004) Faunistical notes on aquatic Heteroptera of Minas Gerais (Brazil): an annotated list of Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha collected near Januaria, MG. Lundiana, 5, 43 - 49." type="journal article" year="2004">Melo &amp; Nieser 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3B4E4B60FFB30D3C1978F8F917F8F89E" author="Pelli, A. &amp; Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. de" box="[820,999,1893,1919]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="67 - 72" refId="ref55515" refString="Pelli, A., Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. de (2006) Nepomorpha and Gerromorpha (Insecta: Heteroptera) from the Serra da Canastra, southwestern Minas Gerais state, Brazil. Lundiana, 7 (1), 67 - 72." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pelli 
<emphasis id="6DABEA83FFB30D3C1922F8FA17BAF89E" box="[878,933,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3B4E4B60FFB30D3C19BCF8F910A8F89E" author="Torres, P. L. M. &amp; Mazzucconi, S. A. &amp; Michat, M. C." box="[1008,1207,1893,1919]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="127 - 153" refId="ref58586" refString="Torres, P. L. M., Mazzucconi, S. A. &amp; Michat, M. C. (2007) Los coleopteros y heteropteros acuaticos del Parque Nacional El Palmar (Provincia de Entre Rios, Argentina): lista faunistica, diversidad y distribucion. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 66, 127 - 153." type="journal article" year="2007">
Torres 
<emphasis id="6DABEA83FFB30D3C1E72F8FA106AF89E" box="[1086,1141,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), but it has also been collected in rivers and stagnant waterbodies connected to lotic ones (reservoirs and pools connected to streams; ponds at waterfall bases) in shaded areas (
<bibRefCitation id="3B4E4B60FFB30D3C1822F831177EF826" author="Vianna, G. J. C. &amp; Melo, A. L." box="[622,865,1965,1991]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="125 - 128" refId="ref58825" refString="Vianna, G. J. C. &amp; Melo, A. L. (2003) Distribution patterns of aquatic and semi aquatic Heteroptera in Retiro das Pedras, Brumadinho, Minas Gerais, Brazil. Lundiana, 4, 125 - 128." type="journal article" year="2003">Vianna &amp; Melo 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3B4E4B60FFB30D3C1921F831103CF829" author="Pelli, A. &amp; Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. de" box="[877,1059,1965,1992]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="67 - 72" refId="ref55515" refString="Pelli, A., Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. de (2006) Nepomorpha and Gerromorpha (Insecta: Heteroptera) from the Serra da Canastra, southwestern Minas Gerais state, Brazil. Lundiana, 7 (1), 67 - 72." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pelli 
<emphasis id="6DABEA83FFB30D3C19E4F83217FFF826" box="[936,992,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
), in a stream with aquatic vegetation (
<bibRefCitation id="3B4E4B60FFB30D3C1A9EF84D1584F80D" author="Souza, M. A. A. &amp; Melo, A. L. &amp; Vianna, G. J. C." box="[210,411,2001,2028]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="803 - 810" refId="ref57968" refString="Souza, M. A. A., Melo, A. L. &amp; Vianna, G. J. C. (2006) Heteropteros aquaticos oriundos do Municipio de Mariana, MG. Neotropical Entomology, 35, 803 - 810. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1519 - 566 X 2006000600013" type="journal article" year="2006">
Souza 
<emphasis id="6DABEA83FFB30D3C1B53F84E1547F80A" box="[287,344,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
), and in a stream and overflow path in agricultural fields mostly exposed to sunlight (
<bibRefCitation id="3B4E4B60FFB30D3D1F2CF84D155EFF50" author="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N." lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="466" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" pagination="43 - 49" refId="ref52862" refString="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N. (2004) Faunistical notes on aquatic Heteroptera of Minas Gerais (Brazil): an annotated list of Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha collected near Januaria, MG. Lundiana, 5, 43 - 49." type="journal article" year="2004">Melo &amp; Nieser 2004</bibRefCitation>
). This species has also been found in streams with gallery forests that run along their margins (
<bibRefCitation id="3B4E4B60FFB20D3D1F2BFF0B150CFF37" author="Pelli, A. &amp; Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. de" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="67 - 72" refId="ref55515" refString="Pelli, A., Nieser, N. &amp; Melo, A. L. de (2006) Nepomorpha and Gerromorpha (Insecta: Heteroptera) from the Serra da Canastra, southwestern Minas Gerais state, Brazil. Lundiana, 7 (1), 67 - 72." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pelli 
<emphasis id="6DABEA83FFB20D3D1ADBFF2714D0FF34" box="[151,207,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F603691FFB20D3D1A8BFF43111AFEFC" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,321]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">At the INR, specimens were collected in standing and slow-moving water along the margins with gallery forests of Pay Ubre Chico Stream and Pay Ubre Grande Stream, in shaded places without aquatic vegetation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
